{
  "modId": 42031.0,
  "modName": "Comment Roaster",
  "summary": "This set of mods (with optional &#39;kill all&#33;&#39; version) simply puts an end to NPC comments about inane things, such as finding items, wandering around with a drawn weapon, and more. Pick and choose what you like. Now with specific dialog deletion options.",
  "descriptionHtml": "This is my set of mods for Skyrim that turn off small annoyances in the &#39;World Interaction&#39; section - NPCs that comment upon seeing you do something/wear something/etc when you&#39;re happening by. Basically, it prevents all NPCs from ever accessing the specified category of comments.\r<br />\r<br />To read about World Interactions, see here: http://elderscrolls.wikia.com/wiki/World_Interactions_%28Skyrim%29\r<br />\r<br />There should be no conflict with these mods UNLESS another mod you have somehow affects World Interaction events; These files do not ADD anything to the game, instead they DELETE the events from ever having the chance to happen.\r<br />\r<br />Current &#39;No Comment&#39; options:\r<br />&#34;No Guard Reaction to Dropping a Weapon&#34; (Sometimes if you drop a weapon in town a guard will make you pick it up and apologize OR SEND YOU TO JAIL IF YOU DON&#39;T BRIBE THEM&#33;)\r<br />&#34;Accidentally Dropped This&#34; (NPC will force-return an item you&#39;ve tossed out of inventory)\r<br />&#34;Dangerous Magic&#34; (NPCs comment if you have dangerous magic active)\r<br />&#34;Drawn Weapons&#34; (NPCs tell you to put your weapon away)\r<br />&#34;Sickness&#34; (NPCs comment if you&#39;re sick)\r<br />&#34;Magical Flames&#34; (NPCs complain about your hands giving off fire)\r<br />&#34;Colorful Magic&#34; (NPCs comment on how &#39;pretty&#39; your bright aura is)\r<br />&#34;College Robes&#34; (NPCs comment warily if you&#39;re wearing college wizard robes)\r<br />&#34;Trash Looting&#34; (Two NPCs talk down at you for &#39;digging through trash&#39;)\r<br />&#34;Nudity&#34; (NPCs tell you to cover up)\r<br />&#34;Sneaking&#34; (NPCs can see you while you&#39;re crouched- noncombat only&#33;)\r<br />&#34;Shouts&#34; (Guards tell you to stop using shouts in town)\r<br />&#34;Found Items&#34; (NPC suddenly runs up to say they wish they had found what you just picked up)\r<br />&#34;Comment Roaster&#34; (Combines ALL OF THE ABOVE INTO ONE MOD)\r<br />&#34;Comment Roaster Vampire Edition&#34; (Combines ALL of the above EXCEPT for comments on illness&#33; Useful for vampires&#33;)\r<br />NEW&#33; - Specific Dialog Deleters\r<br />No Sweetroll Dialog - Guards never utter the stolen sweetroll line.\r<br />No Arrow to the Knee Dialog - Removes the arrow to the knee dialog.\r<br />No Stupid Dog Dialog - Ends all verbal abuse to canines.\r<br />\r<br />I made this mod as a personal &#39;fix&#39;, and released it on the Workshop as a collection. Since other people there have found this useful, I figured I&#39;d put it here, too. The REASONING behind these mods is that some comments can be very distracting, or having NPCs suddenly run up to you just to comment is a little jarring.\r<br />I, myself, have a nervous disorder, so keeping NPCs from running into my face for comments makes me feel less upset about going through towns. Others may find these useful for other reasons.\r<br />\r<br />While the idea has been proposed to me to turn this into a &#39;toggleable&#39; single mod, I have no idea how to make menus or work with MCM. If someone DOES know how and WANTS to combine this into that, let me know via message and I&#39;ll happily talk with you. Chances are I&#39;ll let you go right ahead and release the mod for me, with thanks&#33;\r<br />\r<br />Feel free to share these mods anywhere if someone needs them, just try to remember to link back and don&#39;t upload them as your OWN work.",
